ISLAMABAD, May 08 (APP):The Election Commission of Pakistan (ECP) has issued the initial delimitation for the upcoming Local Government Elections in the Islamabad Capital Territory (ICT).
The list includes 125 union councils, 650 general wards, and 250 womenâ€™s wards. The public has been given a 15-day period, from May 8, to May, 22, to submit their objections or suggestions regarding the preliminary list. The final list of union councils and wards is scheduled to be published on June 9, 2023.
